Comment (policies/secretsmanager_replication_in_sync.rego:41):
**`skip_reason` and `violation` can both fire on the same evaluation (low).** When a secret has e.g. one `Failed` replica and one replica with an unknown future status (`PausedByAWS`), this rule emits `skip_reason` *and* `violation[{"id": "replication_failed"}]` is independently true via line 49. The caller is then in an undefined state: is this record "skipped" or "violating"?

Suggested fix: pick one semantic. Either treat unknown statuses as per-entry skips (filter `unrecognized` out of the violation rule's input and let `Failed` still fire), or short-circuit the entire policy on any unrecognized status (gate the violation with `count(unrecognized_replication_statuses) == 0`). The current behavior is the worst of both.
